COMPONENT NAME: RKM SQL (JYTHON)
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description :
Reverse engineering knowledge module to retrieve definitions of tables, views, system tables and columns from any database.
This knowledge module works on any ISO database, as well as 'non-standard' technologies, such as ODBC for Sage, Rdb, Datacom or any other JDBC or ODBC Driver.
To use this knowledge module, first import it into a project. Create a model and from the the "Reverse Engineer" tab, run this knowledge module under Customized option.
Restrictions:
The mask of tables to reverse must not be empty (default value is '%').
This knowledge module is not compatiable with Selective Reverse.
Retrieval of primary keys is not supported for Microsoft Access due to limitation of JDBC-ODBC bridge. GET_PRIMARY_KEYS option must be set to false when running this RKM.
Note:
- Starting from ODI 12c, all messages will appear in the log file. The USE_LOG and LOG_FILE_NAME options are no longer required.
Set to Yes to Reverse the columns.
Set to Yes to reverse the primary keys.
Set to Yes to reverse the foreign keys.

import java.sql as sql import java.lang as lang import java.util.logging import time
class odiReverse: def __init__(self, iMod, tabPattern, srcConnect,srcCatalog,srcSchema, repoConnect, logger): """ Constructor: iMod: MODEL ID value for the current Model to be reversed tabPattern: Table pattern info [Filter, TableType, AliasRemoveChars] srcConnect: Source connection repoConnect: Repository connection
Example: src = odiRef.getJdbcConnection(SRC) repo = odiRef.getJdbcConnection(DEST) imod = '5111' tabpat = ['%', 'T', 'TRG_'] rev = SnpsReverse(imod, tabpat, src, repo, 1, logfile) rev.startReverse(getcolumns=1, getkeys=1, getfks=1) rev.endReverse() """ self.logger = logger self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO,"Reverse Started.") self.iMod = iMod
# Connect to the source database: self.srccatalog= srcCatalog if self.srccatalog=='' : self.srccatalog=None self.srcschema = srcSchema if self.srcschema == '' : self.srcschema=None
self.srcCx = srcConnect # Connect to the Repostory database: self.repoCx = repoConnect
# Table Pattern information: self.srctabfilter = tabPattern[0] self.aliasremovechars = tabPattern[2] info = 'Reverse Options: Model %s - Filter %s - Selected Table Types %s ' % (self.iMod, self.srctabfilter, tabPattern[1]) self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, info) ## # intialize source metadata ## self.metadata = self.srcCx.getMetaData() self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, 'Driver Name: %s' % self.metadata.getDriverName()) self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, 'Driver Version: %s' % self.metadata.getDriverVersion())
# Filter list of selected table types (only supported types) self.tabtype = self.__gettabletype(tabPattern[1]) info = 'Reverse Options: Filtered Table Types %s ' % (self.tabtype) self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, info)
def startReverse(self, getcolumns=1, getkeys=1, getfks=1): """ Public method to start a reverse set getcolumns, getkeys and getfks flags according to what you want to reverse """ self.__gettables(getcolumns=getcolumns, getkeys=getkeys, getfks=getfks)
def endReverse(self): """ Public Method that should be called to release all opened connections """ self.__del__()
def __gettables(self, getcolumns=1, getkeys=1, getfks=1): """ private gettables(): Starts the Reverse of the Tables retrieves columns, keys and fks according to the flags sent as parameters """ self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, '*** Getting %s List **' %(self.tabtype)) tlst = self.metadata.getTables(self.srccatalog, self.srcschema, self.srctabfilter,self.tabtype) sqltxt = 'insert into SNP_REV_TABLE (MOD_GUID,TABLE_NAME,RES_NAME,TABLE_ALIAS,TABLE_DESC_C,IND_SHOW,TABLE_TYPE) values (?,?,?,?,?,?,?)' ps = self.repoCx.prepareStatement(sqltxt) while tlst.next(): try: table_cat = tlst.getString('TABLE_CAT') except: table_cat = '' try: table_schem = tlst.getString('TABLE_SCHEM') except: table_schem = '' try: table_name = tlst.getString('TABLE_NAME') except: table_name = '' try: remarks = tlst.getString('REMARKS') except: remarks = '' ttype = tlst.getString('TABLE_TYPE') table_type = self.__gettabletype2(ttype) if self.aliasremovechars: table_alias = table_name.replace(self.aliasremovechars, '')[0:128] else: table_alias = table_name[0:128]
self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, 'Table: %s,%s,%s,%s,%s,%s,%s (%s)' % (self.iMod, table_name, table_name, table_alias, remarks, '1', table_type,ttype)) ps.clearParameters() ps.setString(1,self.iMod) ps.setString(2,table_name) ps.setString(3,table_name) ps.setString(4,table_alias) ps.setString(5,remarks) ps.setString(6,'1') ps.setString(7,table_type) ps.executeUpdate() # # Get the columns # if getcolumns: self.__getcolumns(table_name) if getkeys: self.__getkeys(table_name) if getfks: try: self.__getfks(table_name) except: self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, ' Error while getting Foreign Key for : %s table type ( %s, %s)' % (table_name, table_type, ttype))
ps.close() tlst.close() self.repoCx.commit()
def __getcolumns(self, tablename): """ private getcolumns: retrieves columns definition of a specified table """ self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, ' *** Getting Columns for table: %s**' % tablename) clst = self.metadata.getColumns(self.srccatalog, self.srcschema, tablename, '%') sqltxt = 'insert into SNP_REV_COL (MOD_GUID,TABLE_NAME,COL_NAME,COL_HEADING,COL_DESC_C,DT_DRIVER,POS,LONGC,SCALEC,BYTES,COL_MANDATORY,CHECK_FLOW,CHECK_STAT) values (?,?,?,?,?,?,?,?,?,?,?,?,?)' ps = self.repoCx.prepareStatement(sqltxt)
while clst.next(): colpos = 0 coltable = clst.getString("TABLE_NAME") colname = clst.getString("COLUMN_NAME") # coldt = clst.getString("DATA_TYPE") coltypename = clst.getString("TYPE_NAME") colsize = clst.getString("COLUMN_SIZE") try: colsize = int(colsize) except: colsize = None coldec = clst.getInt("DECIMAL_DIGITS") #self.logger.record(coldec) colnull = clst.getString("NULLABLE") try: colnull = int(colnull) except: colnull = clst.columnNullableUnknown try: colremark = clst.getString("REMARKS") except: self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.WARNING, ' ---> REMARKS not suported by the driver') colremark = '' colheading = colname if colremark: colheading = colremark[0:35] try: collen = clst.getInt("CHAR_OCTET_LENGTH") except: self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.WARNING, ' ---> CHAR_OCTET_LENGTH not suported by the driver') try: colpos = clst.getInt("ORDINAL_POSITION") except: self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.WARNING, ' ---> ORDINAL_POSITION not suported by the driver. AutoNumbering.') colpos += 1 colPos=colPos+1 try: colisnull = clst.getString("IS_NULLABLE") if colisnull=='NO': colisnull='1' else: colisnull='0' except: self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.WARNING, ' ---> IS_NULLABLE not suported by the driver. Column set to nullable.') colisnull='0'
self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, ' Column: %s, %s, %d, %s, %d, %d, %d, %s' % (colname, coltypename, colpos, colsize, coldec, collen, colnull, colisnull)) # # Apply updates to the DB # ps.clearParameters() ps.setString(1, self.iMod) ps.setString(2,coltable) ps.setString(3,colname) ps.setString(4,colheading) ps.setString(5,colremark) ps.setString(6,coltypename) ps.setInt(7,colpos) try: ps.setInt(8,colsize) except: ps.setNull(8,sql.Types.INTEGER) ps.setInt(9,coldec) if coltypename.startswith('TIMESTAMP') == 1: ps.setInt(8,coldec) ps.setInt(9,0) try:ps.setInt(10,colsize) except: ps.setNull(10,sql.Types.INTEGER) ps.setString(11,colisnull) ps.setString(12,'1') ps.setString(13,'1') ps.executeUpdate() clst.close() ps.close()
def __getkeys(self, tablename): """ private getkeys: retrieves PK definition of a specified table """ self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, ' *** Getting Keys for table: %s**' % tablename) klst = self.metadata.getPrimaryKeys(self.srccatalog, self.srcschema, tablename)
sqlpk = "insert into SNP_REV_KEY (MOD_GUID,TABLE_NAME,KEY_NAME,CONS_TYPE,IND_ACTIVE,CHECK_FLOW,CHECK_STAT) values (?,?,?,'PK','1','1','1')" sqlpkc = "insert into SNP_REV_KEY_COL (MOD_GUID,TABLE_NAME,KEY_NAME,COL_NAME,POS) values (?,?,?,?,?)"
pspk = self.repoCx.prepareStatement(sqlpk) pspkc = self.repoCx.prepareStatement(sqlpkc)
pkname='' while klst.next(): previouspkname=pkname tablename = klst.getString("TABLE_NAME") colname = klst.getString("COLUMN_NAME") keyseq = klst.getShort("KEY_SEQ") pkname = klst.getString("PK_NAME") if not (pkname): pkname='PK_%s' % tablename
# If a new PK was detected if pkname<>previouspkname: pspk.clearParameters() self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, ' Primary Key: %s' % pkname) pspk.setString(1,self.iMod) pspk.setString(2,tablename) pspk.setString(3,pkname) pspk.executeUpdate() self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, ' Primary Column: %d, %s' % (keyseq, colname)) pspkc.clearParameters() pspkc.setString(1, self.iMod) pspkc.setString(2,tablename) pspkc.setString(3,pkname) pspkc.setString(4,colname) pspkc.setShort(5,keyseq) pspkc.executeUpdate() pspk.close() pspkc.close() klst.close()
def __getfks(self, tablename): """ private getfks: retrieves FKs definition of a specified table (Imported Keys) """ self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, ' *** Getting Foreign Keys for table: %s**' % tablename) klst = self.metadata.getImportedKeys(self.srccatalog, self.srcschema, tablename)
sqlfk = "insert into SNP_REV_JOIN (MOD_GUID,FK_NAME,TABLE_NAME,FK_TYPE,PK_CATALOG,PK_SCHEMA,PK_TABLE_NAME,CHECK_STAT,CHECK_FLOW,IND_ACTIVE) values (?,?,?,?,?,?,?,'1','1','1')" sqlfkc = "insert into SNP_REV_JOIN_COL (MOD_GUID,FK_NAME,FK_COL_NAME,FK_TABLE_NAME,PK_COL_NAME,PK_TABLE_NAME,POS) values (?,?,?,?,?,?,?)"
psfk = self.repoCx.prepareStatement(sqlfk) psfkc = self.repoCx.prepareStatement(sqlfkc)
fkname='' while klst.next(): previousfkname = fkname try: fkname = klst.getString("FK_NAME") except: fkname = '' try: pktablecat = klst.getString("PKTABLE_CAT") except: pktablecat = '' try: pktableschem = klst.getString("PKTABLE_SCHEM") except: pktableschem = '' try: pktablename = klst.getString("PKTABLE_NAME") except: pktablename = '' try: pkcolumnname = klst.getString("PKCOLUMN_NAME") except: pkcolumnname = '' try: fktablecat = klst.getString("FKTABLE_CAT") except: fktablecat = '' try: fktableschem = klst.getString("FKTABLE_SCHEM") except: fktableschem = '' try: fktablename = klst.getString("FKTABLE_NAME") except: fktablename = '' try: fkcolumnname = klst.getString("FKCOLUMN_NAME") except: fkcolumnname = '' try : keyseq = klst.getShort("KEY_SEQ") except: keyseq = '' if fkname <> previousfkname: psfk.clearParameters() self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, ' Foreign Key: %s references (%s, %s, %s)' % (fkname, pktablecat, pktableschem, pktablename)) psfk.setString(1, self.iMod) psfk.setString(2,fkname) psfk.setString(3,fktablename) psfk.setString(4,'D') psfk.setString(5,pktablecat) psfk.setString(6,pktableschem) psfk.setString(7,pktablename) psfk.executeUpdate()
self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, ' Foreign Key Columns: %d, %s=%s' % (keyseq, fkcolumnname, pkcolumnname)) psfkc.setString(1, self.iMod) psfkc.setString(2,fkname) psfkc.setString(3,fkcolumnname) psfkc.setString(4,fktablename) psfkc.setString(5,pkcolumnname) psfkc.setString(6,pktablename) psfkc.setShort(7,keyseq) psfkc.executeUpdate() psfk.close() psfkc.close() klst.close()
def __gettabletype(self,tabPattern): """ private gettabletype: Returns the JDBC table Type according to the Sunopsis TYpe """ selectedtabletypes=[] for snpstype in tabPattern.split(';'): if snpstype=='T': selectedtabletypes +=['TABLE'] elif snpstype=='V': selectedtabletypes +=['VIEW'] elif snpstype=='ST': selectedtabletypes +=['SYSTEM TABLE'] elif snpstype=='AT': selectedtabletypes +=['ALIAS'] elif snpstype=='SY': selectedtabletypes +=['SYNONYM'] elif snpstype=='Q': selectedtabletypes +=['QUEUE'] elif snpstype=='GT': selectedtabletypes +=['GLOBAL TEMPORARY'] elif snpstype=='LT': selectedtabletypes +=['LOCAL TEMPORARY'] else: info = "Ignoring unknown ODI table type '%s'" % (snpstype) self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.WARNING, info)
# Get supported table types supportedtabletypes=[] try: rs = self.metadata.getTableTypes() while rs.next(): supportedtabletypes.append( rs.getString( "TABLE_TYPE" ).upper() ) info = 'Reverse Options: Supported table types: %s' % (supportedtabletypes) self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, info) except Exception, e: info = "Exception received while fetching supported tables type. Any selected table types will be reveresed. Details: %s" % (e) self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.WARNING, info) except: info = "Exception received while fetching supported tables type. Any selected table types will be reveresed." self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.WARNING, info) finally: try: rs.close() except Exception, e: pass
# Is there a valid list of supported table types? filteredtabletypes=[] if len(supportedtabletypes) > 0: # Remove any unsupported table types supportedtabletypes = [item.strip() for item in supportedtabletypes] for t in selectedtabletypes: if supportedtabletypes.count( t ) > 0: filteredtabletypes.append( t ) else: # In case there is no valid list of supported table types, we reverse any selected table types. filteredtabletype = selectedtabletypes
return filteredtabletypes
def __gettabletype2(self,tabletype): """ private gettabletype2: Returns the ODI table Type according to the JDBC TYpe """ if tabletype =='TABLE': return('T') elif tabletype =='VIEW': return('V') elif tabletype =='SYSTEM TABLE' : return('ST') elif tabletype =='ALIAS': return('AT') elif tabletype =='SYNONYM': return('SY') elif tabletype =='QUEUE' : return('Q') elif tabletype =='GLOBAL TEMPORARY' : return('GT') elif tabletype =='LOCAL TEMPORARY' : return('LT') else: info = "Ignoring unknown JDBC table type '%s'" % (tabletype) self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.WARNING, info) return('X')
def __del__(self): """ Finalizer: Close all opened connections """ self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, 'Disconnecting from Source.') if not self.srcCx.isClosed(): self.srcCx.close() self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, 'Disconnecting from Repository') if not self.repoCx.isClosed(): self.repoCx.close() self.logger.log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, 'Reverse End.')

srcCx = odiRef.getJDBCConnection("SRC") srcCatalog= '<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_CATALOG")%>' srcSchema ='<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_SCHEMA")%>'
trgCx = odiRef.getJDBCConnection("DEST") imod = '<%=odiRef.getModel("GLOBAL_ID")%>' tabpat = [ '<%=odiRef.getModel("REV_OBJ_PATT")%>', '<%=odiRef.getModel("REV_OBJ_TYPE")%>', '<%=odiRef.getModel("REV_ALIAS_LTRIM")%>' ]
cols = <%=odiRef.getOption("GET_COLUMNS")%> pks = <%=odiRef.getOption("GET_PRIMARY_KEYS")%> fks = <%=odiRef.getOption("GET_FOREIGN_KEYS")%>
# # START THE REVERSE # logger = odiRef.getLogger() rev = odiReverse(imod, tabpat, srcCx, srcCatalog,srcSchema, trgCx, logger) rev.startReverse(getcolumns=cols, getkeys=pks, getfks=fks) rev.endReverse()
